============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Speed of Light
Formula: c = 299,792,458 m/s in vacuum
Note:    Foundation of special relativity; universal speed limit

Domain:  Chemistry
Topic:   Conservation of Mass
Formula: Reactants mass = Products mass
Note:    Mass is conserved in all chemical reactions

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   E = mc²
Formula: E = mc²
Note:    Mass-energy equivalence; foundation of nuclear physics

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Geology
Topic:   Plate Tectonics
Formula: ~15 major plates on mantle
Note:    Explains earthquakes, volcanoes, mountain formation

